This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Shamika L Moore not in court. 
The Milwaukee County Sheriff's Office has cleared the active warrant, provided the next court date to the defendant, and requested the warrant be withdrawn with approval of Deputy Chief Judge Carl Ashley. MCSO advised defendant to appear in Room 221 of the Safety Building, in person, at 1:00 PM on 11-08-2022.
Return on warrant scheduled for November 8, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
Notice of bond forfeiture mailed to defendant. ($100.00 signature bond)
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a Bench Warrant to be issued REMAND TO COMMISSIONER. Court further orders that bail is forfeited.
Attorney Sam Obscherning in court.  Gregg Herman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a Bench Warrant to be issued.

Defendant Shamika L Moore in court with attorney Sam Obscherning.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Shamika L Moore appeared by video means with Attorney.   Defense counsel has received discovery and DPA offer and requests additional time to review. Defendant to schedule TAD evaluation.   Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 37. All parties are advised effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to a Branch of RESERVE JUDGES.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for August 19, 2022 at 09:00 am.

ADDRESS INFO for Shamika L Moore
Current: 9512 W Thurston Ave, Milwaukee, WI 53225 United States  (Effective: 05-19-2022)
Prior: 1742 South 13th Street, Milwaukee, WI 53204
No conditions set by the court for bail.

Defendant Shamika L Moore in court.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  
The case is adjourned to Br. 37 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 05/19/2022@2:00pm
